Selenium Relative Locators:
above(WebElement) -> Element located above with respect to the specified element
below(WebElement) -> Element located below with respect to the specified element
toLeftOf(WebElement) -> Element located to the left of the specified element
toRightOf(WebElement) -> Element located to the right of the specified element
near(WebElement)

Invoke multiple windows:
  driver.switchTo().newWindow(WindowType.WINDOW) -> It will open in the new window
  driver.switchTo().newWindow(WindowType.TAB) -> It will open in the new tab
  
Take screenshot of a WebElement:
   WebElement ele = driver.findElement(By.xpath(""));
   File file = ele.getScreenshotAs(OutputType.file);
   FileUtils.copyFile(file, new File("./reports/mohan.png");
   
Get the height and width of the WebElement
    ele.getRect().getDimension().getHeight();
    ele.getRect().getDimension().getWidth();
    
 